-- German Stocks Advance, Erasing Earlier Losses; Allianz, Bayer Shares Climb
-- B y   A n d r e w   R u m m e r
-- 2012-02-23T08:31:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/german-stocks-advance-erasing-earlier-losses-allianz-bayer-shares-climb.html
German stocks rose for the first
time in three days, erasing their earlier losses, as  Allianz SE 
and Bayer AG advanced.  The benchmark DAX Index climbed 0.4 percent to 6,871.12 at
9:30 a.m. in  Frankfurt , having earlier dropped as much as 0.2
percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
